1.title: Crab-eating Macaque
1.plot: In this episode, the Junior Rangers attempt to return a crab-eating macaque to the wild. Their knowledgeable friend, Ranger Rocky, assists them in their journey through the rainforest.

2.title: Smooth-coated Otter
2.plot: The Junior Rangers take a baby smooth-coated otter to the rainforest to find its home. Unfortunately, a group of hungry crocodiles have their eyes on the little otter.

3.title: Sumatran Orangutan
3.plot: Leo finds a playful young orangutan in his garden. With the orangutan in tow, the Junior Rangers travel to the Indonesian island of Sumatra to look for the orangutan's mother.

4.title: Koala
4.plot: Leo and Hero meet a koala in their garden. The Junior Rangers head Down Under to find a home for the koala, but a pack of wild dogs gets in their way.

5.title: Malayan Pangolin
5.plot: The Junior Rangers make a trip to the jungle to reunite a shy pangolin with its mother. There, the Junior Rangers come face to face with a ferocious tiger.

6.title: Giant Panda
6.plot: The Junior Rangers take a young giant panda to China to search for a bamboo forest. But what happens when the panda strays off on its own?

7.title: Komodo Dragon
7.plot: Hero comes across an egg in the garden. To Leo's surprise, a baby Komodo dragon hatches from the egg instead of a baby bird.

8.title: Sun Bear
8.plot: Leo, Katie, Hero and a sun bear cub set off for the rainforest to find the cub's mother. Alas, they end up trapped in an overgrowth of stinky Rafflesia flowers. Can the Junior Rangers, Hero and sun bear cub overcome the overpowering odour of the Rafflesias and escape?

9.title: Sumatran Rhinocerous
9.plot: A game of hide and seek results in the discovery of a baby Sumatran rhino. Leo, Katie and Hero go to Sumatra, Indonesia to return the rhino to its mother.

10.title: White-bellied Woodpecker
10.plot: Today's mission: return a white-bellied woodpecker to its rightful place in the rainforest. The Junior Rangers try to do just that, but come under attack by a swarm of wasps. Will the Junior Rangers succeed in their mission, or face the sting of defeat?

11.title: Reticulated Python
11.plot: While playing in the garden, Leo and Hero stumble upon a reticulated python and its eggs. The Junior Rangers drive to the rainforest to find a suitable home for the python, but an aggressive hippo makes the task a lot more difficult.

12.title: Australian Pelican
12.plot: Katie identifies a large-beaked bird in the garden as an Australian pelican. The Junior Rangers bring the pelican to a lake and track down the pelican's parents.

13.title: Malayan Tapir
13.plot: The Junior Rangers are on a quest to reunite a lost Malayan tapir with its mother. But their visit to the rainforest leads them to another encounter with - the Malayan tiger.

14.title: Dawn Bat
14.plot: Leo chances upon a dawn bat while sketching in his garden. The Junior Rangers embark on a search after sundown for the dawn bat's cave.

15.title: Dugong
15.plot: An unusual guest shows up in Leo's swimming pool-a dugong. Come along with the Junior Rangers as they seek a safe home for the dugong. But can they accomplish that while warding off a ship of dugong hunters?

16.title: White-bellied Sea Eagle
16.plot: Leo spots a white-bellied sea eagle while flying his kite. Understanding that the sea eagle doesn't belong in their garden, the Junior Rangers take the sea eagle to a lake where it can find food-and its partner.

17.title: Satin Bowerbird
17.plot: Leo discovers that a satin bowerbird has been stealing blue objects from him and his family. Realizing that the satin bowerbird might be lost, the Junior Rangers set out to bring the satin bowerbird back to its bower.

18.title: Pygmy Hippo
18.plot: A pygmy hippo appears in the garden pond. The Junior Rangers hit the road to send the hippo home, but their journey is delayed by a sticky situation involving quicksand.

19.title: Honey Bee
19.plot: A honey bee drops in on Leo's picnic. The Junior Rangers buzz down to the forest to guide the honey bee back to its beehive, but an encounter with some wasps could prove too much for the Junior Rangers to handle.

20.title: Bottlenose Dolphin
20.plot: A baby bottlenose dolphin is the last animal Leo expects to see in his garden pond. But when the unexpected happens, the Junior Rangers start on an expedition to find the dolphin's mother.

21.title: Barn Owl
21.plot: A barn owl scares Leo in the garden. The Junior Rangers depart for the grasslands to find a better hunting place for the barn owl.

22.title: Asian Elephant
22.plot: Leo comes across a baby Asian elephant while planting an apple tree. To find the elephant's mother, the Junior Rangers explore the lowland forest.

23.title: Indian Peacock
23.plot: Leo, Katie and Hero get to know a feathery new friend-an Indian peacock. They bring the peacock to the rainforest to look for peahens, but end up crossing paths with two jungle cats.

24.title: Wild Boar
24.plot: The Junior Rangers bring a wild boar in their garden back to the forest. There, Ranger Rocky advises the Junior Rangers to find the boar's sounder, which is a group of female wild boars and their young children.

25.title: Leatherback Sea Turtle
25.plot: A fun game of table tennis leads to the surprise discovery of a baby sea turtle and some sea turtle eggs. Can the Junior Rangers return the baby sea turtle and eggs to the beach while keeping them safe from hungry raccoons?

26.title: Greater Mouse-deer
26.plot: The Junior Rangers bring a greater mouse-deer back to its home in the rainforest. But can the Junior Rangers rescue the mouse-deer when it gets caught in an animal trap?

27.title: Yellow-footed Rock Wallaby
27.plot: Who's that hopping into the garden? Why, it's a yellow-footed rock-wallaby-and its baby. The Junior Rangers hightail it to Australia to send mother and child home, but will a couple of flat tires throw a spanner in the works?

28.title: Vervet Monkey
28.plot: A vervet monkey shows up as an uninvited guest to one of Leo's picnics. The Junior Rangers head to the savannah to bring the monkey home, but the trip takes a nasty turn when they fall into an animal trap.

29.title: Marvellous Spatuletail
29.plot: Leo, Katie and Hero travel to Peru to take a marvellous spatuletail home. But what can they do when the hungry bird falls into a deep sleep?

30.title: Clouded Leopard
30.plot: A trip to the rainforest becomes necessary when a clouded leopard cub turns up in the garden. The Junior Rangers search for the cub's mother, but are set back when the cub gets entangled in some tree vines above water.

31.title: Atlantic Puffin
31.plot: Leo meets an Atlantic puffin in the garden while playing with his remote-controlled car. The Junior Rangers decide to take the puffin home to Iceland. There, Leo has a mishap at the edge of a cliff.

32.title: Asian Palm Civet
32.plot: After an Asian palm civet steals Hero's food, the Junior Rangers set off to bring the civet back to where it belongs. The trip takes them to the rainforest, a durian plantation and a run-in with a wild boar.

33.title: Raccoon
33.plot: Leo catches a raccoon digging around in his trash. The Junior Rangers take the raccoon back to the forest where it can find its own food. However, some unfriendly raccoons make things difficult for Leo and company.

34.title: Yellow-eyed Penguin
34.plot: A yellow-eyed penguin wanders into Hero's kennel. The Junior Rangers head to New Zealand to find the penguin's home, but can they prevent tourists from disturbing yellow-eyed penguins on the beach?

35.title: Yellow-crested Cockatoo
35.plot: A yellow-crested cockatoo joins Leo and Hero's game of musical statues. After learning more about the bird, the Junior Rangers travel to the rainforest to take it home.

36.title: Whitespotted Bamboo Shark
36.plot: Katie finds out that a big fish in the garden pond is a whitespotted bamboo shark. The Junior Rangers sail to the Pacific Ocean to find a coral reef for the bamboo shark to live in.

37.title: Sunda Slow Loris
37.plot: When a Sunda slow loris lands in the garden, the Junior Rangers quickly learn that they have to return it to the wild. Will they manage to find the slow loris a home? Or will the slow loris end up as a snack for a hungry sun bear?

38.title: Reindeer
38.plot: Join the Junior Rangers as they race across the tundra to reunite a lost reindeer calf with its herd. However, a river crossing might prove too tiring for the young reindeer.

39.title: Estuarine Crocodile
39.plot: A visit to the mangrove swamp is in order when Leo and Hero find a baby estuarine crocodile in the garden. Can the Junior Rangers find the baby crocodile's nest while avoiding the adult crocodiles that roam the swamp?

40.title: Plantain Squirrel
40.plot: Leo finds a baby plantain squirrel eating his seed collection. The Junior Rangers drive to the forest to locate the squirrel's nest and mother.

41.title: Common Tree Frog
41.plot: A common tree frog hops into the garden one wet and rainy day. Leo, Katie and Hero take the frog to the forest, where Ranger Rocky directs them to find the frog's breeding ground.

42.title: California Sea Lion
42.plot: A young California Sea Lion makes a surprise appearance during Leo's basketball game. Later, a voyage to find the sea lion's home turns into a daring rescue on the high seas.

43.title: Indian Star Tortoise
43.plot: The Junior Rangers have a brush with a poacher as they try to return an Indian Star Tortoise to its home in the scrub forest.

44.title: Goliath Birdeater Spider
44.plot: The Junior Rangers go to the rainforest to find a new home for a goliath birdeater spider. But can the Junior Rangers scare off a pair of weasels who are preying on their eight-legged friend?

45.title: Malayan Water Monitor
45.plot: A swim in the garden brings Leo and Hero up close and personal with a Malayan water monitor. The Junior Rangers set out to search for the monitor's home, but will their jeep survive a river crossing after a jeep float gets punctured?

46.title: Leafy Seadragon
46.plot: Imagine Leo's surprise when he realizes that a piece of seaweed in his aquarium is actually a leafy seadragon.

47.title: Equatorial Spitting Cobra
47.plot: Leo, Katie and Hero travel to the forest to return an equatorial spitting cobra to its home. Things heat up when the Junior Rangers and slithery serpent are ambushed by mongooses.

48.title: Blue Pansy Butterfly
48.plot: Leo finds a blue pansy caterpillar, and the Junior Rangers set off to find a home for it. On the way, they come upon other blue pansy caterpillars and butterflies, whose home will be destroyed soon.

49.title: Orca
49.plot: Ranger Rocky invites the Junior Rangers along on an adventure to return an orca to the sea. But the task becomes twice as hard when they come across a second orca that is stranded on the beach.

50.title: Green Iguana
50.plot: The discovery of a green iguana in the garden leads to an adventure in the rainforest. The Junior Rangers want nothing more than to find the iguana's home, but a hungry hawk has other plans for the iguana.

51.title: South African Cheetah
51.plot: Leo spots a South African cheetah cub in his garden. The Junior Rangers journey to the savannah to locate the cheetah cub's mother, but the cheetah cub is captured halfway by illegal hunters.

52.title: Electric Eel
52.plot: Leo is shocked to find an electric eel in the garden pond. The Junior Rangers travel to South America to return the eel to its home, but their mission takes a wild turn when they meet an anaconda.

53.title: Rothschild's Giraffe
53.plot: The Junior Rangers bring a young Rothschild's giraffe to the savannah to find it a good home. However, the expedition comes to a standstill when the Junior Rangers' jeep gets bogged in mud.

54.title: Reef Manta Ray
54.plot: sail to find the manta ray a home in the ocean, but what happens when Ranger Rocky gets stuck in a sea jelly bloom?

55.title: Eastern Spotted Skunk
55.plot: Leo comes across an eastern spotted skunk while playing a game of mini-golf in the garden. The Junior Rangers pop by the prairie to find a suitable home for the skunk, but an unfriendly coyote could put a dent in their plans.

56.title: Malayan Colugo
56.plot: Leo's paper plane crashes into a young Malayan colugo. The Junior Rangers search the rainforest for the colugo's mother, but the mission comes to a halt when they chance upon a forest fire.

57.title: Malayan Tiger
57.plot: The Junior Rangers travel to the rainforest to reunite a Malayan tiger cub with its mother. But when the cub goes missing in some tall grass, the Junior Rangers have to put their heads together to find it.

58.title: Mola
58.plot: Ranger Rocky entrusts the Junior Rangers with a mission-return a mola to the ocean. The Junior Rangers take up the challenge, but find themselves having to wing it when some seagulls start pecking the mola.

59.title: Scalloped Hammerhead Shark
59.plot: The Junior Rangers head to the ocean to find a home for a young scalloped hammerhead shark. Unfortunately, the adventure takes a wet turn when the hammerhead shark gets caught in a shrimp net.

60.title: Oriental Pied Hornbill
60.plot: Leo meets an oriental pied hornbill while picking apples in his garden. To find the hornbill's nest, the Junior Rangers set out for the rainforest once again.

imdb.title: Leo the Wildlife Ranger
plot: Join Leo and friends as they go on exciting adventures around the world and explore exotic locations and learn fun facts about animals and nature!::Tang Chi Sim
